The apparent QE was measured in the same autoclave and the conditions were kept the same as those for a typical photocatalytic test, while the autoclave was then irradiated by a 300-W Xenon lamp (Newport) by using band-pass filters of 385 ± 40, 437 ± 10, 575 ± 25, 650 ± 20, 750 ± 20 and 1000 ± 10 nm, respectively. Numbers of photons were calculated from the irradiation powers in each wavelength region measured by a light metre at the corresponding wavelengths. The apparent QE can be calculated by using the equation1QE%=Numberofevolvedhydrogenmolecules×2Numberofincidentphotons×100%.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
